        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 14 at 4:50PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 449 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Conner, or 21 miles southeast of Hamilton, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, half-inch size hail, and heavy
rainfall .

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible. Loacalized flash flooding and/or ponding on
roadways and in low-lying areas possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Darby, Conner, Sula, Grantsdale, Skalkaho Pass, Charlos
Heights, Corvallis, and Como.

This includes Highway 93 S between mile markers 7 and 48.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
